<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN364">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>vāṭā mālai pāṭiṉi yaṇiya</l>
<l>pāṇaṉ ceṉṉik kēṇi pūvā</l>
<l>verimaru ṭāmaraip perumalar tayaṅka</l>
<l>maiviṭai yirumpōttuc centī cērttik</l>
<l>kāyaṅ kaṉinta kaṇṇakaṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>naṟavuṇ cevvāy nāttiṟam peyarppa</l>
<l>vuṇṭun tiṉṟu mirappōrk kīntu</l>
<l>makiḻkam vammō maṟampō rōyē</l>
<l>yariya vākalu muriya peruma</l>
<l>nilampaka vīḻnta valaṅkaṟ palvēr</l>
<l>mutumarap pottiṟ katumeṉa viyampuṅ</l>
<l>kūkai kōḻi yāṉāt</l>
<l>tāḻiya peruṅkā ṭeytiya ñāṉṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While unfading garlands adorn the songstresses (1),</l>
<l>while big blossoms of flame-like lotus</l>
<l>that did not bloom in wells sway on the heads of the bards (2f.)</l>
<l>putting a big male black ram on the red fire, (4)</l>
<l>while moving on the tongues of [our] toddy-drinking red mouths (6)</l>
<l>fat pieces large in extent that melt with spices, (5)</l>
<l>eating, feasting [and] giving to those who beg (7)</l>
<l>let us make merry, come, you of valorous battle! (8)</l>
<l>[Such things] are rightful, great man, as soon they will become difficult (9)</l>
<l>– at the time when we reach the big cremation ground with urns (13)</l>
<l>where the owl fowl do not end (12)</l>
<l>that give sound harshly from the hollows of old trees (11)</l>
<l>with many swaying roots that descend so that the ground is split. (10)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
